choices.text:
what are the types of verbs?
There are several types of verbs, including transitive, intransitive, regular, irregular, and helping verbs. Transitive verbs require an object to complete their meaning, while intransitive verbs do not. Regular verbs follow a predictable pattern when adding -ed or other verb forms, while irregular verbs have unique forms that must be memorized. Helping verbs are used with the main verb to form compound tenses and questions.
